This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses a framework for reasoning about objectives in machine learning. It may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it deals with the theoretical foundations of machine learning. The paper's discussion of thermodynamics suggests that it may also be relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on developing a formal correspondence between machine learning and thermodynamics suggests that it may also be relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
